      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HOT ROD HARRY (2) gets his best draw for some time but has produced some good results from those wider barriers including a win at this circuit and distance last month and a 1.7m second after racing parked last week. Should get every chance this time. SIR RICHARD LEE (10) added to his strong form when he beat HOT ROD HARRY at this circuit and distance last week, giving him two wins and two placings from his past four outings. Draws on the second line but is going well. EXCLUSIVE HUSTLER (6) was very good in winning the G3 Golden Guitar Final from a second line draw two back at Tamworth and is suited going up to a distance where he has recorded a win and a placing in two attempts at it here. BASILISK BOB (11) has had no luck of late, suffering interference and breaking at the latest appearance after he was held up at a vital stage prior. Awkward draw but he is worth another chance.",
